msgstr ""
"Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\n"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Today’s topic is about solving problems.\n"
"\n"
"Every family has challenges, but working together helps us find calm, good solutions — at home, at school, in the community and online."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "How can problem solving help you and your family?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Greetings, everyone.\n"
"\n"
"Today's topic is problem solving.\n"
"\n"
"We all know that in life there are times where we face problems, and we all know in a way that when we find ourselves in these situations, it is difficult to think of immediate positive solutions.\n"
"\n"
"Therefore, it is important that when we are facing problems we take a pause, we breathe, keep calm and think of problem-solving skills that we may use."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"As caregivers, we sometimes think we need to fix every problem by ourselves. And teens can think the same! \n"
"\n"
"By involving your teen, you strengthen your relationship as well as their confidence. Together you can overcome anything."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_female_4.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can problem solving keep your teens safe? It did for @data.characters.media_female_4.name - tap play to hear her story"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"I did not have a good relationship with my daughter. I was always shouting at her, and she was refusing to go to school.\n"
"\n"
"Only when I started spending One-on-One time with her, I realised that she did not want to go to school because she was being bullied at school. We sat down and used the steps of problem solving. We identified the problem, and figured out solutions together: “What can I do as a parent so you can attend school and feel safe?”\n"
"\n"
"We agreed I would go talk to the teacher to find a way forward. We really found the solutions together, and we are closer now."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f2_grandmother.name
#.      @data.characters.f2_son_15.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Problem-solving together is an important skill for every family. Let’s see how @data.characters.f2_grandmother.name and @data.characters.f2_son_15.name handle a problem calmly and find a plan together."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string _@data.characters.f2_grandmother.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "_@data.characters.f2_grandmother.name is coming home from work._"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_son_15.name! should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f2_son_15.name! Look at all those dishes, why did you not wash those like we agreed!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name… should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Sorry, @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name… I can explain, there is this guy from my class, on WhatsApp he…"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "(_thinking_): Let me take a pause… just breathe…"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I am sorry, @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Now tell me, what happened on WhatsApp?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "This boy in class shared a video of me in a WhatsApp group, and now everyone is making fun of me."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_son_15.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I am sorry to hear that, but I am glad you told me, @data.characters.f2_son_15.name. It does not mean you can leave your chores. After we speak, you need to do the dishes so I can make dinner. But first, what do you think we should do about the bully problem?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He makes me so angry, I just want to hit him. Or maybe I should tell my teacher?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Hmm… What do you think will happen if you hit him? And if you tell your teacher?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I don’t know. If I hit him we may get into a big fight and I could get hurt or get into trouble at school. But if I tell my teacher they may call me a snitch… Maybe you could talk to the teacher?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That sounds like a good idea. I could also go talk to his parents if you want me to."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name, should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name, please don’t! Maybe I can skip school tomorrow instead?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"No, Thabo — you can’t miss school. \n"
"I have an idea! Let’s practise how you might reply if classmates tease you. Do you want to try ignoring it or making a small joke?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Maybe I’ll just say, “Don’t worry, I was testing gravity — it still works!”"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Haha! That’s good! Remember, keeping calm or laughing along takes away their power."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "_A week later…_"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "How are things going at school now?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "It is going better, the boy deleted the video from the WhatsApp group chat. But he is still being really mean to me."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_son_15.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"I am sorry to hear that, @data.characters.f2_son_15.name. I will be speaking to your teacher tomorrow — your school knows how to handle this safely.\n"
"If that does not work, we will try something else."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, thank you, @data.characters.f2_grandmother.role_name. At least I know you are on my side."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When you face a problem, take a few deep breaths to help you stay calm. \n"
"Then, try to handle the problem using these four steps!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "KNOW IT"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Identify the problem."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "SOLVE IT"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Think of possible solutions and what would happen if we used them."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "TRY IT"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Choose a solution and try it out."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "TEST IT"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Did it work? Great! If it did not work, then try another solution."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_mother.name,
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Now let’s try problem-solving ourselves.\n"
"Imagine that @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name got a phone as a gift from a boy, and her mother, @data.characters.f1_mother.name, feels worried about it."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_mother.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "What could @data.characters.f1_mother.name do to handle the situation when @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name got a phone from a boy?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Ground @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name for a month"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Return the phone and save up together to buy a new one"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Talk to @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name about safe sex"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name’s should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Listen to @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name’s side of the story"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Take a deep breath before reacting"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That didn’t work... Let's try something else."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You cannot go out for the next month"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Uuugh… that’s so unfair, I did not do anything wrong!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_mother.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"This is a great option! \n"
"\n"
"Parenting teens is really hard. Often there are no simple and easy solutions, but now @data.characters.f1_mother.name learned she can talk to her daughter about these things."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I am not trying to accuse your friend or be jealous. I am worried that when someone gives a gift it is hard to say 'no' when they ask something in return – like sex. If you want to have a phone, we will save up together so you can make your own decisions without owing him anything."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That makes sense, thank you, @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "This makes me realise we should talk about boyfriends and protecting yourself. Many teens your age get pregnant or become HIV positive. Let’s go to the clinic so you can talk with the nurse to learn how you can stay safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Okay, thank you, @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Please tell me your side of the story. I am here to listen."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Okay… I can explain. He said it was just a gift."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_mother.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"This is a great option! \n"
"\n"
"Parenting teens is really hard. Often there are no simple and easy solutions, but now @data.characters.f1_mother.name learned she can talk to her daughter about these things.\n"
"\n"
"Before, she worried alone, now they can come up with solutions together!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Now that I have had a moment to calm down, let’s talk. How did you get this phone?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "He gave it to me after school. I didn’t want to start a fight."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When something bad happens, we often get upset and blame. But what our teens really need is someone to help find solutions together. \n"
"\n"
"Listen to them, accept how they see and feel things, and thank them for trusting you.\n"
"\n"
"Teaching your teen how to deal with problems will help them for the rest of their lives. What a gift!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**Here are some examples of problems other caregivers solved with their teens:**\n"
"\n"
"- My teenager does not want to go to school\n"
"- My teenager is on their phone too much\n"
"- I am worried my teenager will get pregnant or will get someone pregnant\n"
"- I am worried about what my teen does online\n"
"- My teenager is hanging out with bad friends"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Your home activity this week is to teach your teenagers the steps for problem-solving and use them together when a problem comes up."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**Remember to use the four steps of problem-solving:** \n"
"💭 Step 1: KNOW IT (identify problem)\n"
"📋 Step 2: SOLVE IT (identify solutions) \n"
"⚒️ Step 3: TRY IT (try one) \n"
"🎯 Step 4: TEST IT (try another solution if this one did not work)"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can you solve one problem together with your teen this week - using the four steps?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's great! Working together with your teen will bring so many good outcomes for you both."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I think so"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You can do it! Try it out with a ‘small’ problem that may come up, so you can see how it works before tackling a bigger challenge."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's okay. Just remember that when a situation feels overwhelming, it can really help to use the four steps of problem solving with your teen to break the problem down."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"We all have problems, but they don’t define us! You can choose to address challenges and try different solutions together with your teen. \n"
"This shows your teen that they are never alone and gives them a key skill to use at home, with friends, and for life!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_son_2.name's should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can you make an impact on your community with these skills? Hear @data.characters.media_son_2.name's story"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When my father introduced the problem-solving steps to me, it helped me with my family, but it also helped me with my friends.\n"
"\n"
"I told my friends about the steps, and now when we are arguing we sit down and everyone comes up with solutions. We then look for the negatives and positives of each solution, and we agree “okay let’s try this one.”\n"
"\n"
"My friends even took it to their own homes, and it is helping with their families as well!\n"
"\n"
"It is great when others listen to you and accept your ideas even though you are young. We can all bring that harmony with our friends and family."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Well done for taking time for yourself today. 🎉"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Here is a short video to help you slow down before you go"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When everything feels like it is falling apart And you can't help but raise your voice When all the frustrations are beginning to start Remember that you have a choice\n"
"\n"
"Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Remember all we have to be grateful for Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Because I really couldn't love you more\n"
"\n"
"You can take pause, you can count to 10 Play a game or do something fun You can phone a friend, someone to confide in Remember you're not the only one\n"
"\n"
"Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Remember all we have to be grateful for Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Because I really couldn't love you more\n"
"\n"
"Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Remember all we have to be grateful for Let's slow down Take a few deep breaths Because I really couldn't love you more Because I really couldn't love you more"
msgstr ""
